        "client_msg_id": "5ed1234e-63a2-4537-acd9-5a7f0e668169",
        "text": "for the cleanest diff ASAP, now I'm thinking about not trying to clean up everything in the git (although we will need to do so at some point -- due to the thousands of extra commits in there compared to SVN, and the fact that we don't really \"push back\" the changes to SVN as-is, but a patch has been applied in the past with manual tweaks .. and the two codebases has deteriorated quite a bit in the past years), but experimenting with:\n• starting with a blank PO file form SVN\n• fill that up from git\nsomething like, although `msgattrib --clear` is just pseudo command for now:\n```msgattrib --clear svn.po -o blank.po\nmsgmerge --no-fuzzy-matching --compendium=git.po blank.po blank.po -o svn.po```\nthis would reduce the accidental sorting and metadata mismatch issues, only keeping the updated translations. <@U01N3ET8N82>, thoughts on this?",
        "team": "T01DW9DLB2A",
        "user_team": "T01DW9DLB2A",
